I have never written a review before, but this was so bad that i had to. I’ve had an absurd amount of pizza in my life, and this was one of the worst. The crust had no flavor and there was barely any sauce- it tasted like cardboard. The “cheesy garlic bread” was just French bread with cheese in the middle... nothing special about it. I could have made a better Caesar salad than the one i paid for. Definitely could’ve made everything better than what i paid for. Isn’t the point of paying money to order food for it to taste better than if you made it? I work in the restaurant industry, so it takes a lot for me to justify writing a negative review. But you could do at least something to make everything i tried taste better than the absolute bare minimum quality.

Beware online orders.  Ok pizza but awful service.  Ordered online through their website  for a few people to pick up. I get a text to confirm the order and it will be ready in 15-30 min. After 20 min I get  another text saying it might take longer. Annoying but at least I got a heads up.  When get there after 1 hour  they say they never got the order. I’ve already been charged on my credit card mind you. The guy gives me a look like I’m SOL. I confirm the online service they use the guy say yes they use that and then continues to stare at me a like I’m an idiot for showing up wanting food from a takeout place.......  How about apologizing the online order was not received on your end and offer to take my order in person. Sheesh..... if they don’t want my order online or in person then I’m never giving this place my business. To many places to force them to give you service.  Update: Slice online ordering service says the promo manager told them they had my food ready and it was never picked up!!!  What a load of BS! They refused to refund. Just plain fraudulent.

I have been eating here for past 7 years.  I've been working in the west loop and i am always looking for inexpensive food. This is the best place you can go to have some delicious Italian food.  old school. It's been around a long time.  the feeling you get when entering any number of ancient Greek or Italian joints in Chicago.  i couldn't find any info on when it opened so i'll have to ask  next time i stop in.  like today.  for under $5 i got a bevvies & an enormous slice cut into little squares (?) which came with a cup of cream of spinach soup that was even better than the pizza.  who does that?  salads, Italian beefs & subs, Iaccoca, and everything in between.  delicious foods & a full wallet.  that's what i'm talking about.
